CLASS LOADING\
\
BootStrap Class Loader\
- $JAVA_HOME/jre/lib/rt.jar			- This is the runtime jar and includes the core java library\
\
Extension Class Loader\
- $JAVA_HOME/jre/lib/ext/*.jar\
\
\
Application Class Loader\
$classpath\
\
\
User-Defined Class Loader\
\
\
Parent-Delegation Model\
Bootstrap CL is parent of Extension CL which is parent of Application CL which is parent of User-Defined CL\
\
\
\
When is a class or interface loaded by the JVM\
- new instance of the class is created				[this only applies to a class and not to an interface]\
- a static method of the class/interface is invoked\
- a static field of the class/interface is accessed\
- one of its subclass is loaded					[an interface can be loaded when its subclass or sub-interface is loaded]\
- if the class/interface is run directly from the command line\
- can be loaded via reflection\
\
\
Note: compile time constants of a class do not cause a class to be loaded since they were compiled in at compile time and not at run time\
\
\
\
Class Object\
\
The Class Object contains meta information of a class as follows:\
String getName()\
Class getSuperClass()\
boolean isInterface()\
Class[] getInterfaces()\
ClassLoader getClassLoader()\
\
The following have a Class Object\
- Class\
- Interface\
- Primitives\
- void keyword\
- Arrays\
\
\
\
\
LINKING\
\
Verification Steps\
 - final classes are not subclassed\
 - final methods are not overridden\
 - No illegal method overloading\
 - bytecode integrity (jump instruction)\
\
\
Preparation Steps\
 - Storage allocation for static fields\
 - initialize fields with default values\
 - OutOfMemoryError if no space in memory\
 - Instance creation\
	instance fields are initialized after static fields\
\
Resolution Steps\
 - resolve symbolic references and load them\
 - Permissions and Correctness (referenced fields exist, are of the right type and the current class has the permission to access the fields)\
\
 - this is dynamic linking\
\
Symbolic References - are logical references stored in a Constant Pool that are replaced with direct references at run time\
\
Constant Pool - is made up of Symbolic References, compile time constants and string literals\
\
\
Dynamic Linking can be\
- Eager Loading :	happens after preparation step in Linking process \
				referenced classes are loaded and initialized before current class initialization completes\
- Lazy Loading :	happens after Initialization process (i.e. on-demand) \
				referenced classes are loaded when the statement referencing them is encountered\
				symbolic references in the class being executed are then replaced with direct references\
				this is the default implementation of most JVM\'92s\
\
\
\
\
INITIALIZATION\
\
- initialize static fields with user defined values\
- An Interface is only initialized if one of its static methods is accessed OR one of its fields which is a non-compile time constant is accessed\
\
